+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P02-T025 (DocumentVersion schema + migration + rollback; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Twenty-fifth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S2-P02, Canonical Document and version chain), one task per run. Goal: implement an append-only DocumentVersion chain for the CanonicalDocument identity from T024 -- history is never overwritten; content, attachments, status, and date changes are recorded per version. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; schema/DDL-only, no worker, D1, or R2 change, and the migration is authored and verified on an isolated in-memory copy only (it is NOT applied to the production D1 adp-mirror). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/schemas/: document_version.migration.sql (cn_documents with canonical_id primary key, title_norm, sources_json, current_version_no, created_at, first_seen_at; plus cn_document_versions with version_id primary key, canonical_id, an append-only version_no, content_hash, status, doc_date, artifact_keys_json, created_at, and UNIQUE(canonical_id, version_no); three indexes on canonical_id, content_hash, and status; and a cn_meta document_version_schema = adp.document_version.v0_1 marker -- every statement IF NOT EXISTS / INSERT OR IGNORE, so it is idempotent) and document_version.rollback.sql (reverse DROP of the indexes and tables plus a scoped delete of only the one cn_meta key, so a pre-existing cn_meta is preserved). Acceptance verified on an isolated copy (evidence/ADP-S2-P02-T025/test-results/migration_test.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the before/after row and relationship checks hold (after migrating a production-like copy that already has cn_meta, inserting one canonical document and a two-version chain yields docs = 1 and versions = 2 with 0 orphan versions by a left join, the history is preserved so v1's content hash is not overwritten by v2, UNIQUE(canonical_id, version_no) is enforced so a duplicate version_no is rejected, and the schema marker is registered); the migration is idempotent (a second apply does not error or duplicate); and the rollback succeeds on the isolated copy (the migration objects are all removed, the pre-existing cn_meta row is kept, and the schema marker key is removed). Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 rows read 0 / written 0, R2 bytes 0 / operations 0, model_calls 0; the migration is not yet applied to production. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P02-T024 (CanonicalDocument identity + repost merge + dedup)
 
 - Twenty-fourth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S2-P02 (Canonical Document and version chain), one task per run. Goal: distinguish the same document, a repost, an attachment, a revision, and an entirely different event. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; rules-only, no worker/D1/R2 change. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/canonicalize.py (deterministic identity -- doi:<normalized DOI> or ttl:<sha256 of the normalized title> -- plus repost merge that preserves every source's raw artifact, revision tracking, and collision detection), CANONICAL_DOCUMENT_SPEC.md, schemas/canonical_document.schema.json, and canonical_doc_index_500.json (the canonical document index for the real 500-item sample). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S2-P02-T024/test-results/canonical_tests.txt): the same document re-run does not add a document (a fixture of two items with the same DOI collapses to one canonical document, and the real 500 items yield 498 canonical documents with 2 duplicate items collapsed and 0 collisions); a repost merges but the artifacts are preserved (a fixture of the same DOI from nature and chinanews yields one merged document with sources [nature, chinanews] and both raw artifacts kept); a revision (the same DOI with a vN suffix) stays one document with the revision recorded; entirely different events stay separate documents; and collisions are explainable (a ttl identity whose normalized titles differ is flagged with a reason and a resolution of falling back to the DOI or a content hash). Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
